Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.47,0:00:03.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnArial Black\pos(316,325)\fad(400,0)}Obey the Rules and manners\Nto have a fun Duel!!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.38,0:00:05.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What on Earth {\i1}is{\i0} this?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.73,0:00:08.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Barrier of Orichalcos...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.44,0:00:12.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The ones imprisoned within this boundary
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.45,0:00:15.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,can't escape until someone wins the Duel!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.49,0:00:18.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the one to lose...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.14,0:00:21.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His soul will be sealed within the barrier!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.08,0:00:22.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What did you say?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.48,0:00:23.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't screw around!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.15,0:00:24.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Big brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.54,0:00:28.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mokuba!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.29,0:00:49.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Sometime ago, for the sake of living, we left behind our happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.25,0:00:56.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We deceived ourselves, clinging to this mere illusion as we danced...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.55,0:01:02.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}With closed eyes, at the end of the horizon,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.81,0:01:08.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I was searching for your smiling face...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.27,0:01:16.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We embrace our dreams and continue on...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.28,0:01:22.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}within the swaying traces of memories...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.21,0:01:29.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Someday, I will once again grasp hold of
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.30,0:01:37.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}these feelings I have locked away in my heart... Now...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.05,0:02:00.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Wake Up! Critias"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.79,0:02:03.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Big brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.52,0:02:04.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Big brother!!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.66,0:02:05.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Big brother!!!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.25,0:02:09.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's a considerably elaborate trick you've pulled off.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.56,0:02:11.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Seto Kaiba...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.27,0:02:15.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have any idea of just how long I've been waiting for this day to arrive?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.84,0:02:17.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You said you were Amelda, correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.97,0:02:22.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The appearance of Duel Monsters as well as buying out all the stocks of Kaiba Corporation...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.60,0:02:24.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was all your doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.64,0:02:25.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who knows?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.12,0:02:30.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then what's the point of this little farce?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.46,0:02:31.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought I told you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.29,0:02:34.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is for the sole purpose of retrieving your soul.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.21,0:02:37.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Put an end to the stupid jokes already!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.60,0:02:39.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Jokes," was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.97,0:02:41.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.67,0:02:45.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't walk away from this Orichalcos Barrier.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.97,0:02:51.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll take your soul as atonement for the sins you and Kaiba Corporation have committed!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.56,0:02:55.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sins? What the hell are you going on about?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.57,0:03:08.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong with you, Yugi?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.57,0:03:12.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a bit worried about Pegasus.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.51,0:03:13.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Worried?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.17,0:03:17.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Pegasus told us in the video letter, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.27,0:03:19.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That he was being followed by someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.67,0:03:20.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.27,0:03:23.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If that's really true,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.31,0:03:26.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,there's a chance Pegasus is in danger.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.35,0:03:28.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Danger?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.27,0:03:35.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I Summon Balrog in Attack Mode!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.64,0:03:46.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Its Attack Points went up!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.51,0:03:47.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.90,0:03:51.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Barrier of Orichalcos increases the Attack
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.94,0:03:55.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,of all Monsters on my field by 500 points!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.63,0:03:56.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.71,0:04:01.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Also, whenever you have a Fire-Attribute Monster with Balrog on the field,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.57,0:04:04.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,its Attack goes up by 500 points.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.22,0:04:05.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.14,0:04:08.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Balrog himself is of the Fire element!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.43,0:04:14.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,2000 Attack Points?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.65,0:04:18.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Balrog! Attack God of Destruction - Vasago!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.87,0:04:32.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Any Monster destroyed by Balrog, at the end of the Battle Phase,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.04,0:04:36.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,will be Special Summoned on my field in Attack Mode.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.46,0:04:38.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And will become a Fire-Attribute Monster.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.77,0:04:41.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But they will lose their Special Effects.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.18,0:04:50.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And with the increase in Fire-Attribute Monsters,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.64,0:04:53.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Balrog's Attack Points will further increase!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.94,0:04:56.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shit!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.81,0:04:59.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whenever Brother's Monsters are destroyed,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.67,0:05:02.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the opponent's Monsters will increase in number!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.34,0:05:08.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I set a reverse card. Turn over.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.16,0:05:11.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}This strategy using Balrog is no joke...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.70,0:05:14.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}So he wasn't just talking big?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.66,0:05:16.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.67,0:05:21.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}As long as I can destroy Balrog,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.63,0:05:24.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}the Monsters he Special Summoned will also disappear.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.51,0:05:27.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'll make him an offering for the Virus Combo next turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.43,0:05:29.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.18,0:05:31.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.07,0:05:36.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I Summon Pitch-Dark Dragon in Defense Mode!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.52,0:05:41.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Also, I set a reverse card!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.27,0:05:44.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Deck Destruction Virus of Death, is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.65,0:05:49.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know exactly what you're thinking right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.03,0:05:54.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because I've analyzed\Nall the information I could find on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.21,0:05:59.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see... You must be well-prepared.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.21,0:06:02.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess those ignorant \Nto the ways of the world
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.29,0:06:06.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,must put in extra effort when recklessly challenging those stronger than them.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.09,0:06:08.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You're{\i0} the one who doesn't know the ways of the world!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.13,0:06:09.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.27,0:06:16.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look at this.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.64,0:06:21.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Humph! And what exactly is that piece of garbage supposed to prove?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.86,0:06:25.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure it {\i1}looks{\i0} like\N a piece of garbage to {\i1}you{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.86,0:06:28.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So if it's {\i1}not{\i0} garbage, then {\i1}what{\i0} is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.70,0:06:32.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is a...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.95,0:06:35.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...memento of my little brother!!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.08,0:06:39.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My little brother was...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.12,0:06:41.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...killed by your company!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.59,0:06:47.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My country used to be beautiful...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.36,0:06:52.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even now, I recall the beautiful streets of my country...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.51,0:06:57.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But before I knew it, I was staring straight into the pits of Hell...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.37,0:07:17.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Look out!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.54,0:07:23.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You're still holding onto that thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.40,0:07:28.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But you gave it to me as a present for my birthday, Brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.49,0:07:30.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}This is my treasure!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.26,0:07:31.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You little...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.80,0:07:33.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Once this war ends,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.23,0:07:35.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'll buy you as many toys as you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.69,0:07:36.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.76,0:07:39.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Can we hurry up and... end this war then...?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.10,0:07:42.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's going to be over soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.90,0:07:47.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And we can play soccer together!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.40,0:07:49.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.03,0:07:57.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Now! Let's move!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.30,0:08:25.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You alright, boys?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.23,0:08:31.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Wow! Cool!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.76,0:08:32.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.59,0:08:34.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}This is a brand new tank!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.16,0:08:36.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The newest combat tanks created by Kaiba Corporation!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.90,0:08:39.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Its functions excel\Nthose of the enemy's.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.37,0:08:43.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Kaiba Corporation has\N agreed to work with us!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.49,0:08:45.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We can have as many weapons\Nas possible!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.62,0:08:48.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We {\b0}will{\b1} win! We'll win this!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.63,0:08:50.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And we can end this war then!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.93,0:08:52.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.01,0:08:53.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Wait for me!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.76,0:08:54.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.46,0:08:59.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Mama...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.80,0:09:02.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Brother, you're crying.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.06,0:09:03.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Not true!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.02,0:09:06.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The one crying is your stomach.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.81,0:09:08.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'll get you some food.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.43,0:09:13.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.13,0:09:15.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Come on, Miruko!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.96,0:09:20.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Get on!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.53,0:09:22.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's safe in here!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.04,0:09:22.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.80,0:09:27.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Mama's pendant!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.03,0:09:28.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Hang on!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.03,0:09:35.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Miruko!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.93,0:10:20.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Miruko...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.23,0:10:30.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}MIRUKO!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.83,0:10:33.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}MIRUKO!!!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.43,0:10:50.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know who that man is?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.46,0:11:00.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Gozaburo Kaiba.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.29,0:11:02.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}He's the president of Kaiba Corporation.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.43,0:11:05.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Kaiba... Corporation?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.72,0:11:10.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Yes. He is the true murderer of your little brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.59,0:11:16.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}This man gave new weapons to both sides in order to test their combat strength.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.48,0:11:17.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}No way...!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.59,0:11:23.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Do you want to take revenge on that man?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.21,0:11:46.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No way...!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.54,0:11:50.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My heart died that day.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.37,0:11:52.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is my revenge!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.24,0:11:56.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My brother...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.17,0:11:57.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This isn't my brother's fault!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.61,0:11:59.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mokuba...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.32,0:12:01.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was Gozaburo who sold the weapons!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.64,0:12:03.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And my big brother hated him for that!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.77,0:12:06.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So he bought out Kaiba Corporation's stocks!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.37,0:12:11.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He wanted to use the wealth and power he obtained to create a better future!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.50,0:12:15.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And that was my brother's... and Kaiba Corporation's redemption!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.71,0:12:17.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Redemption{\i0}, you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.42,0:12:21.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right! For all the kids around the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.38,0:12:22.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Big brother built Kaiba Land!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.93,0:12:24.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't make me laugh!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.37,0:12:28.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that going to bring back my little brother? My parents?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.43,0:12:30.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.72,0:12:32.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Enough, Mokuba.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.94,0:12:34.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, Big brother...!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.84,0:12:41.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kaiba Corporation destroyed peace in order to obtain its wealth.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.54,0:12:43.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Duel Disk you created...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.80,0:12:46.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As well as the enormous investment you placed in order to conduct this plan of yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.70,0:12:47.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No...!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.70,0:12:50.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even the food you've been eating throughout your entire lives...!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.80,0:12:52.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The clothes on your backs, even!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.91,0:12:56.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All of it was bought using the money from Kaiba Corporation!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.42,0:12:59.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Money obtained by taking others' {\i1}lives{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.42,0:13:04.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll make you pay for your sins, with your {\i1}soul{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.17,0:13:06.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Revenge, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.24,0:13:12.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have indeed taken over Kaiba Corporation's, as well as Gozaburo's crimes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.61,0:13:15.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have no intentions of denying this.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.11,0:13:18.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But even if you're gonna\N Duel me because of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.06,0:13:21.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you have your own way of seeing the truth, and you can continue Dueling that way!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.21,0:13:26.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All I can do is Duel my way to show you who's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.49,0:13:30.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, I'll be the right one! You can't defeat me!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.44,0:13:34.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I activate the Trap Card, Proclamation of the Royal Palace!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.94,0:13:36.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As long as this card remains active,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.62,0:13:39.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,all Trap Cards on the field will be negated!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.74,0:13:42.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Trap Cards will be negated?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.96,0:13:47.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That Deck Destruction Virus of Death you worked so hard to bring out is now useless.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.14,0:13:49.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Turn over.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.94,0:13:51.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.74,0:13:54.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Balrog, attack Pitch-Dark Dragon!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.90,0:14:01.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now your only defending Monster is gone!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.71,0:14:05.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then I use God of Destruction - \NVasago to Direct Attack you!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.57,0:14:13.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Brother's Life Points...!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.71,0:14:18.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the destroyed Pitch-Dark Dragon becomes my Monster.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.67,0:14:27.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I don't have any Monsters in my hand that doesn't require a sacrifice.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.30,0:14:30.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Everything depends on the card I draw next turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.07,0:14:32.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.00,0:14:35.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's here...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.94,0:14:39.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll create my future with my own two hands!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.87,0:14:43.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Magic Card activate! Life-Shaving Card Treasure!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.52,0:14:45.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now I have five cards in my hand!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.80,0:14:49.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look! This is the power that will determine my future!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.34,0:14:52.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I activate the Ritual Magic, Descent of White Dragon!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.94,0:14:59.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I sacrifice Monsters worth Level Four or higher in order to let Knight of White Dragon descend!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.42,0:15:00.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.17,0:15:04.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I sacrifice Blue-Eyes White Dragon!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.67,0:15:09.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ritual Summon! Knight of White Dragon!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.38,0:15:14.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Also, I Special Summon Blue-Eyes from the Graveyard using Resurrection of the Dead!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.07,0:15:23.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Knight of White Dragon, attack Pitch-Dark Dragon!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.48,0:15:31.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now that I've removed a Fire-Attribute Monster, Balrog's Effect causes it to lose Attack Points!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.74,0:15:36.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I use Blue-Eyes to attack Balrog!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.14,0:15:49.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And if you sacrifice Knight of White Dragon,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.64,0:15:56.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am able to Special Summon another Blue-Eyes White Dragon from my deck!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.85,0:16:01.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I believe you said it was impossible for me to win.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.90,0:16:04.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I return those words to you in {\i1}earnest{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.86,0:16:06.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.11,0:16:12.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was an admirable attack, Seto Kaiba.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.07,0:16:15.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But a flame radiates for only a brief moment before it goes out.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.45,0:16:17.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Still bragging, even after all {\i1}this{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.54,0:16:23.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Magic Card, activate! Pot of Greed!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.08,0:16:25.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I draw two cards from my deck!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.63,0:16:29.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And then I activate the Magic Card, Aetonix Flame!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.59,0:16:35.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Impossible...!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.30,0:16:37.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Both{\i0} Blue-Eyes were taken out at the same time!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.01,0:16:45.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aetonix Flame destroys all non-Fiend-Type and non-Fire-Attribute Monsters on the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.27,0:16:50.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can then Special Summon a Fiend-Type Monster or a Fire-Attribute Monster to the field from my Graveyard.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.37,0:17:01.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Also, I activate the Magic Card, Fire Whip!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.44,0:17:12.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fire Whip Special Summons all Monsters destroyed on this turn
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.76,0:17:17.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to my side of the field as Fire-Attribute Monsters.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.30,0:17:19.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My Blue-Eyes have...!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.30,0:17:24.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You have the honor of your trusted Blue-Eyes delivering you the final blow.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.71,0:17:27.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For you, there can't be {\i1}anything{\i0} better than {\i1}this{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.65,0:17:40.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And due to the two Blue-Eyes becoming Fire-Attribute Monsters,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.28,0:17:41.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Balrog becomes more powerful as per his Effect.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.58,0:17:47.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Due to the effect of Aetonix Flame,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.08,0:17:50.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't go into battle this turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.54,0:17:52.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I suppose I just spared your life a bit longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.21,0:17:55.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I set a reverse card and end my turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.80,0:18:01.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now draw a card, Seto Kaiba.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.22,0:18:03.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This will be the last draw of your {\i1}life{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.02,0:18:06.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Now that I've lost my God Card,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.69,0:18:09.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I have no card to turn the tables...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.94,0:18:13.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Absurd...! Is it all going to end in a place like {\b0}this{\b1}...?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.32,0:18:16.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Such a  thing...!\N I will {\b0}not{\b1} accept such a thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.37,0:18:28.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What {\i1}is{\i0} this place?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.80,0:18:36.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is this statue?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.63,0:18:40.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Am I supposed to pull it out?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.78,0:18:56.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.49,0:18:58.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know your name.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.28,0:19:02.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your name is Critias!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.12,0:19:09.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.08,0:19:10.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.37,0:19:21.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Was I hallucinating?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.34,0:19:27.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What is this card?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.60,0:19:30.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Impossible...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.05,0:19:32.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Why is there a card I don't recognize in my deck?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.98,0:19:34.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Still...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.86,0:19:38.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I know the power this card holds!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.57,0:19:41.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll bet on this card to turn the tables!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.87,0:19:44.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go! The Fang of Critias!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.87,0:19:47.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What did you say?! That card is...!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.00,0:19:49.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Due to its Special Ability,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.63,0:19:52.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can Summon a Fusion Monster merged with a Trap Card!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.50,0:19:56.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Impossible!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.59,0:19:59.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A Fusion Monster merged with a Trap Card, you said?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.30,0:20:02.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have just transcended common sense!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.47,0:20:08.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come forth! Death Virus Dragon!!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.81,0:20:12.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Death Virus Dragon?" For real?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.85,0:20:16.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Death Virus Dragon destroys all Monsters on the field
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.32,0:20:20.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,with 1500 Attack Points or more!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.37,0:20:32.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Take this! Death Virus Dragon, Direct Attack!!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.04,0:20:37.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I win, Amelda!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.28,0:20:43.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Reverse card, activate! Quick-Play Magic, Contagion of Madness!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.59,0:20:44.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.62,0:20:51.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Contagion of Madness!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.29,0:20:59.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It deals damage to the opponent player's Life Points equal to half of the attacked Monster's Attack Points!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.61,0:21:11.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Big brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.88,0:21:14.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A draw?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.00,0:21:16.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You better remember this!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.13,0:21:19.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I {\i1}shall{\i0} have my revenge on you!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.93,0:21:34.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's up? Out of gas?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.64,0:21:35.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,O-Oi!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.47,0:21:40.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's with him?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.14,0:22:02.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The houses lined down the street drifting by being dyed red
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.50,0:22:10.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If I notice pain, it'll turn into happiness
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.11,0:22:21.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Every time people wipe away tears, they understand bonds
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.18,0:22:31.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The warm strength that you gave me will change into kindness
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.66,0:22:40.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Overflowing feelings don't stop
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.94,0:22:50.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'll live while I feel it, for me to be myself
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.84,0:22:59.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Healed by overflowing friendship
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.99,0:23:05.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Our fated encounter is a truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.51,0:23:14.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}and someday we'll be able to understand each other
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.12,0:23:23.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,While Kaiba-{\i1}kun{\i0} was busy fighting against Amelda of Doma,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.21,0:23:28.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the limousine was taking us to see Pegasus at Industrial Illusions.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.26,0:23:32.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But now the car has stopped\Nat an old gas station,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.55,0:23:34.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and the driver went out\Nand never came back.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.51,0:23:37.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have a bad hunch.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.27,0:23:39.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.02,0:23:41.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's a group of motorcyclists\Ncoming this way!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.48,0:23:43.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next time!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.11,0:23:44.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"The Unexpected Enemy"
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.27,0:23:45.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Duel standby!
